'''
2.Indexing and slicing operations
-->index tells about the position of a character
   we have two types of indexing
   1.Zero based indexing
    It goes from left to right
    it runs from 0 to n-1 where n represents total number of characters

   2.negative indexing
    it goes from right to left
    it runs from -1 to -n
'''
p='python'
print(p[2])
print(p[-4])

#write a program to check if the last but one character from  the
#given input string is a vowel
#true or false is the expected output
num1=input()
num= num1[-2]
print(num in 'aeiou')

'''
slicing:
obtaining a substring from the given string is called slicing
'''
m="python"
#string[start:stop+1:step] nothing is mandatory over here
print(m[1:5])
print(m[1:5:2])
print(m[::2])
print(m[::1])
print(m[::3])

'''
negative indexing and slicing

'''
print(m[::-1])
print(m[-1:-2:-2])
'''
"""
string methods
"""
# Python String Methods â€” 


---

## ðŸ“˜ Overview

Python provides many built-in string methods for text processing, validation, formatting, and transformation. This guide covers:

* Common and frequently used methods
* Rare but useful methods
* Code examples
* Practice questions

---

## ðŸ“Œ 1. Casing Methods

| Method         | Description                            | Example                          |
| -------------- | -------------------------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| `upper()`      | Converts to uppercase                  | `'hello'.upper()` â†’ `'HELLO'`    |
| `lower()`      | Converts to lowercase                  | `'HeLLo'.lower()`                |
| `title()`      | Converts to title case                 | `'hello world'.title()`          |
| `capitalize()` | First letter uppercase, rest lowercase | `'hELLO'.capitalize()`           |
| `swapcase()`   | Swaps case                             | `'Hello'.swapcase()` â†’ `'hELLO'` |

---

## ðŸ“Œ 2. Checking / Testing Methods

Return **True/False**.

| Method           | Checks if...               | Example                   |
| ---------------- | -------------------------- | ------------------------- |
| `isalpha()`      | alphabetic characters only | `'abc'.isalpha()`         |
| `isdigit()`      | digits only                | `'123'.isdigit()`         |
| `isalnum()`      | alphanumeric               | `'abc123'.isalnum()`      |
| `islower()`      | lowercase                  | `'abc'.islower()`         |
| `isupper()`      | uppercase                  | `'ABC'.isupper()`         |
| `isspace()`      | whitespace only            | `'   '.isspace()`         |
| `istitle()`      | title case                 | `'Hello World'.istitle()` |
| `isnumeric()`    | numeric characters         | `'â…£'.isnumeric()`         |
| `isdecimal()`    | decimal digits             | `'123'.isdecimal()`       |
| `isidentifier()` | valid Python identifier    | `'name_1'.isidentifier()` |

---

## ðŸ“Œ 3. Searching Methods

| Method         | Description                                 | Example                    |
| -------------- | ------------------------------------------- | -------------------------- |
| `find()`       | Returns index of substring (or -1)          | `'hello'.find('l')` â†’ `2`  |
| `rfind()`      | Last occurrence                             | `'hello'.rfind('l')` â†’ `3` |
| `index()`      | Like `find()` but raises error if not found | `'hello'.index('e')`       |
| `rindex()`     | Last index, with error                      | `'hello'.rindex('l')`      |
| `startswith()` | Checks prefix                               | `'hello'.startswith('he')` |
| `endswith()`   | Checks suffix                               | `'hello'.endswith('lo')`   |

---

## ðŸ“Œ 4. Counting & Repeating

| Method       | Description        | Example                     |
| ------------ | ------------------ | --------------------------- |
| `count()`    | Counts occurrences | `'banana'.count('a')` â†’ `3` |
| `* operator` | String repetition  | `'ha' * 3` â†’ `'hahaha'`     |

---

## ðŸ“Œ 5. Replace & Split

| Method              | Description       | Example                     |
| ------------------- | ----------------- | --------------------------- |
| `replace(old, new)` | Replace substring | `'a-b-c'.replace('-', '+')` |
| `split()`           | Splits into list  | `'a,b,c'.split(',')`        |
| `rsplit()`          | Splits from right | `'a:b:c'.rsplit(':',1)`     |
| `splitlines()`      | Splits by newline | `'a\nb'.splitlines()`       |

---

## ðŸ“Œ 6. Joining

| Method           | Description                  |
| ---------------- | ---------------------------- |
| `join(iterable)` | Joins elements into a string |

**Example:**

```python
'-'.join(['a', 'b', 'c'])   # 'a-b-c'
```

---

## ðŸ“Œ 7. Stripping (Removing characters)

| Method     | Description                  | Example            |
| ---------- | ---------------------------- | ------------------ |
| `strip()`  | Remove spaces from both ends | `'  hi  '.strip()` |
| `lstrip()` | Left strip                   | `'  hi'.l          |
'''

